1567<div>

1568<h2>

1569Selecting the Perfect Cabinet</h2>

1570

1571

1572<p>

1573Cabinets reign in the chaos that comes with a home, making clutter disappear behind beautifully crafted doors with soft-close hinges. For <em>

1574<strong>

1575kitchens</strong>

1576</em>

1577, we carry a variety of base, wall, and pantry cabinets to keep your pots, pans, dishware, and utensils organized. <a href="https://vevano.com/resource-center/how-to-organize-spices/" target="_blank">

1578Arrange spices</a>

1579, snacks, and cereals&nbsp;so they&rsquo;re neatly ordered and ready to use at any moment. Stock rags, hand towels, and dish soap safely out of the way until you need them.&nbsp;</p>

1580

1581

1582<p>

1583For <em>

1584<strong>

1585bathrooms</strong>

1586</em>

1587, cabinets create a stylish, functional focal point. Secure soap, shampoos, cleaners, and more to declutter the space quickly and efficiently. Keep rolls of toilet paper and other hygienic products close enough to use, but out of sight. Available in multiple sizes, whether your bathroom is large or small.&nbsp;</p>

1588

1589

1590<p>

1591Cabinets also make additions to other areas of the home including <a href="https://vevano.com/resource-center/laundry-room-ideas/" target="_blank">

1592laundry rooms</a>

1593, bar areas, theater rooms, and offices. Store everything ranging from papers to towels to refreshments. Stylish cabinet doors add a touch of polish while concealing whatever you need to store.&nbsp;</p>

1594

1595

1596<h3>

1597Cabinet Styles to Match Your Design Vision&nbsp;</h3>

1598

1599

1600<p>

1601Cabinets are the foundation of style in any room, whether that&rsquo;s the kitchen, bathroom, or laundry room. Eyes are drawn to the color, <a href="https://vevano.com/resource-center/how-to-choose-cabinet-hardware/" target="_blank">

1602cabinet hardware</a>

1603, and the design of the doors. It&rsquo;s difficult to achieve a <em>

1604<strong>

1605farmhouse</strong>

1606</em>

1607 look in the kitchen or bathroom without the appropriate storage elements. <em>

1608<strong>

1609Modern</strong>

1610</em>

1611 requires sleek lines and an uncluttered appearance. <em>

1612<strong>

1613Contemporary</strong>

1614</em>

1615 is fresh, taking on popular colors and styles. <em>

1616<strong>

1617Classic</strong>

1618</em>

1619 is almost traditional, timeless in appearance and style. <em>

1620<strong>

1621Industrial</strong>

1622</em>

1623 is a practical design, focused on functionality and minimal ornamentation. <em>

1624<strong>

1625Transitional</strong>

1626</em>

1627 is a blend of styles, personalized to your tastes. Each style relies on certain <a href="https://vevano.com/resource-center/cabinet-finishes/" target="_blank">

1628cabinet finishes or colors</a>

1629, <a href="https://vevano.com/resource-center/cabinet-door-styles-101/" target="_blank">

1630cabinet door styles</a>

1631, and hardware to make the look come to life.&nbsp;</p>

1632

1633

1634<h3>

1635Cabinet Color Ideas&nbsp;</h3>

1636

1637

1638<p>

1639What colors do you gravitate to? Does the open, fresh look of white grab your attention? We have multiple shades of white from antique white to bright white to glossy whites. Does the flexibility of gray pull you in? Our selection of grays and dove is for you. Do you love the mood and contrast that dark tones provide? Check out our hues of rich espresso and chocolate. Or, does the <a href="https://vevano.com/resource-center/wood-kitchen-cabinet-types/" target="_blank">

1640natural look of wood cabinets</a>

1641 spark your interest? We carry a range from light to dark wood for you to peruse.&nbsp;</p>

1642

1643

1644<p>

1645A growing trend is to add more dimension by mixing colors with two-tone cabinets. Can&rsquo;t choose between white and gray? Love the contrast of dark shades and white together? No problem &ndash; have both! The two-tone dynamic works well in kitchens, laundry rooms, master bathrooms, or bar areas. You can do this by having the base cabinets be the darker color with the lighter color being used on the wall cabinets. Another option is to make an island one color while the rest of the cabinets are another.&nbsp;</p>

1646

1647

1648<p>

1649We have a cabinet collection for you with a range of colors, hues, and stains to add the perfect touch to your home. Plus, our designers are always happy to talk about color options for your home. Contact us by email, live chat, or call 1-855-483-2629.&nbsp;</p>

1650

1651

1652<h3>

1653Which Cabinet Door Type is Best?&nbsp;</h3>

1654

1655

1656<p>

1657Our <a href="https://vevano.com/resource-center/cabinet-door-styles-101/" target="_blank">

1658cabinet door types</a>

1659 are split into three main categories: slab, Shaker, and raised panel. Here&rsquo;s a quick definition for each one.&nbsp;</p>

1660

1661

1662<ul>

1663

1664 <li>

1665<em>

1666<strong>

1667Slab door</strong>

1668</em>

1669 &ndash; This minimal design is completely smooth and flat, providing a smooth look in a room. It&rsquo;s also referred to as a European style cabinet door. It&rsquo;s most often used in modern, contemporary, and industrial styles.&nbsp;</li>

1670

1671 <li>

1672<a href="https://vevano.com/resource-center/shaker-style-cabinets/" target="_blank">

1673<em>

1674<strong>

1675Shaker door</strong>

1676</em>

1677 </a>

1678&ndash; This type features a flat center panel that&rsquo;s framed by squared edges to add an element of dimension. It&rsquo;s one of the most popular styles because of its simplicity and design flexibility. It can be used in modern, contemporary, transitional, classic, or farmhouse styles with ease.&nbsp;</li>

1679

1680 <li>

1681<em>

1682<strong>

1683Raised</strong>

1684</em>

1685 <em>

1686<strong>

1687panel door</strong>

1688</em>

1689 &ndash; At its core, this style means the center panel of the door is raised, while the area surrounding the door is contoured to be lower. Raised panels come in different designs with differences in how much profiling and contouring there is.&nbsp;</li>

1690

1691</ul>

1692

1693

1694<p>

1695&nbsp;</p>
